문서: (CNN) -- Sergio Garcia knows the law well. He has a law degree and passed the California bar exam -- on his first try. Now he wants to practice that law, giving advice and taking on cases. "I'm fighting for my American dream," he said. Wednesday was a landmark day -- his first case before the California Supreme Court. But he's not able to act as a lawyer in front of the justices, because the law he loves is not on his side. Garcia, 36, has been an undocumented immigrant since he was brought to the United States as a child from his native Mexico, and that means he cannot get a law license.
@highlight
Undocumented immigrant Sergio Garcia fights for his California law license
@highlight
Is it legal for an undocumented immigrant to practice law?
@highlight
"I'm fighting for my American dream," Sergio Garcia says
@highlight
DOJ: How can someone without legal status become licensed as a lawyer? 
The case is being closely watched for the precedent it could set, not just for @placeholder, but the nation.

